This conversation discussed various aspects of coastal resilience and the development of a "Coastal Barometer" to monitor and guide the economic health of Delaware's coastal economy. The conversation highlighted the distinction between hard and soft resilience projects, noting their benefits and drawbacks, as well as the potential for hybrid projects. The importance of understanding the dynamism of the coastal economy and its risks and opportunities was emphasized. The proposed Coastal Barometer would provide real-time updates on the economy's health, supporting informed decision-making and infrastructure development. Future research needs were also discussed, including the impacts of climate change, the cost-effectiveness and protection benefits of different resilience systems, the permitting process, and gathering narratives from affected community members. Overall, investing in coastal resilience through adaptive and cost-effective strategies was deemed crucial for the future prosperity and sustainability of Delaware's coastal economy.
